.\" termin.al-name: cd
.\" termin.al-usage: cd [path]
.\" termin.al-summary: Change this shell pane's virtual directory.
.TH CD 1 "" "termin.al" "termin.al Manual"
.ftr B R
.ftr I R
.ftr BI R
.SH NAME
cd \- Change this shell pane's virtual directory.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
cd [path]
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
Changes the virtual working directory owned by the current shell pane. Relative paths resolve from that pane's current directory; paths beginning with
.B ~
resolve from the virtual home directory, and
.B ..
walks toward that home.
.PP
With no path, cd selects
.BR ~ .
The command changes only path state and emits no text output.
.SH FAILURES
More than one path, an option before
.BR -- ,
an invalid path, a missing path, a file path or a locked path is rejected without changing the directory.
.SH NOTES
Each shell pane retains its own directory across focus, swap, rotation and layout changes. A newly created shell pane starts at
.BR ~ .
Pane state is in-memory and is not restored after a page reload.
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
$ cd projects
$ cd ../notes
$ cd
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
pwd(1), ls(1), pane(1)
